'''2011年巴林反政府示威活动'''为从2011年2月14日开始持续至2011年底发生在[[巴林|巴林]]的示威活动，为[[2010－2011年阿拉伯世界的反政府示威|2010－2011年阿拉伯世界的反政府示威]]的一部分。初期示威者要求政府提供体面的工作和生活，要求公民享有大的政治自由度和赋予[[什叶派|什叶派]]平等的权利和地位等内容的民主政治改革，不久在巴林人口中占大多数的什叶派穆斯林提出了推翻[[逊尼派|逊尼派]]王室统治的要求。<ref>{{cite web | language = zh-cn | publisher = 环球网 | title = 巴林为示威死亡者举行葬礼 哀悼者要求王室下台 | url = http://world.huanqiu.com/roll/2011-02/1507712.html | date = 2011-02-18 | accessdate = 2011-02-18 | archive-date = 2011-02-21 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110221043905/http://world.huanqiu.com/roll/2011-02/1507712.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>

2月17日，巴林出动军队镇压了示威者。3月14日，在海合會的支持下，沙特和阿联酋的1500名军警进驻巴林帮助该国平息内乱，哈馬德國王宣佈全國進入三個月緊急狀態。这些举措受到了一些国际组织和外国政府的谴责。

警察对待手无寸铁的示威者的方式被描述为是“残酷的”，描述者有医生和写博客的。<ref>Press release (30 March 2011).  [http://www.scoop.co.nz/stories/WO1103/S01049/usa-emphatic-support-to-saudi-arabia.htm "USA Emphatic Support to Saudi Arabia"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.scoop.co.nz/stories/WO1103/S01049/usa-emphatic-support-to-saudi-arabia.htm |date=20171019083111 }}.  Zayd Alisa (via [Scoop).  Retrieved 15 April 2011.</ref><ref>Cockburn, Patrick (18 March 2011).  [http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/the-footage-that-reveals-the-brutal-truth-about-bahrains-crackdown-2245364.html "The Footage That Reveals the Brutal Truth About Bahrain's Crackdown – Seven Protest Leaders Arrested as Video Clip Highlights Regime's Ruthless Grip on Power"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/the-footage-that-reveals-the-brutal-truth-about-bahrains-crackdown-2245364.html |date=20171107114141 }}. ''[[The_Independent|The Independent]]''. Retrieved 15 April 2011.</ref>警察还在夜晚袭击什叶派居住的地区，在路障点殴打什叶派人，并拒绝让那些受伤的示威者得到救治。<ref>Wahab, Siraj (18 March 2011).  [http://arabnews.com/middleeast/article320723.ece "Bahrain Arrests Key Opposition Leaders"] {{Wayback|url=http://arabnews.com/middleeast/article320723.ece |date=20120307000356 }}. ''Arab News''. Retrieved 15 April 2011.</ref><ref>Law, Bill (22 March 2011). [http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-12817106 "Bahrain Rulers Unleash 'Campaign of Intimidation'"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-12817106 |date=20171203174855 }}. ''Crossing Continents'' (via [[BBC_News|BBC News]]). Retrieved 15 April 2011.</ref><ref>{{registration required|date=April 2011}} [http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/3f6c2574-54b6-11e0-b1ed-00144feab49a.html "UK – Bahrain Union Suspends General Strike"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/3f6c2574-54b6-11e0-b1ed-00144feab49a.html |date=20110827095806 }}. ''[[Financial_Times|Financial Times]]''.  22 March 2011. Retrieved 9 April 2011.</ref><ref>Chick, Kristen (1 April 2011). [http://www.csmonitor.com/World/Middle-East/2011/0401/Bahrain-s-calculated-campaign-of-intimidation "Bahrain's Calculated Campaign of Intimidation – Bahraini Activists and Locals Describe Midnight Arrests, Disappearances, Beatings at Checkpoints, and Denial of Medical Care – All Aimed at Deflating the Country's Pro-Democracy Protest Movement"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.csmonitor.com/World/Middle-East/2011/0401/Bahrain-s-calculated-campaign-of-intimidation |date=20171009220832 }}. ''[[The_Christian_Science_Monitor|The Christian Science Monitor]]''.  Retrieved 15 April 2011.</ref>政府也摧毁了几座什叶派[[清真寺|清真寺]]，因这些地方曾是反政府抗议的聚集点。抗议者们则进行绝食以表达不满。<ref>Staff writer (18 April 2011).  [http://www.presstv.ir/detail/175441.html "Bahraini Forces Demolish Two Mosques"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.presstv.ir/detail/175441.html |date=20110728091833 }}.  Press TV.  Retrieved 19 April 2011.</ref>至今已有800多人受到逮捕，<ref>[http://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/applying-pressure-on-bahrain/2011/05/09/AF3sV6bG_story.html Applying pressure on Bahrain] {{WebCite|url=https://www.webcitation.org/6B8lU6de1?url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/applying-pressure-on-bahrain/2011/05/09/AF3sV6bG_story.html |date=20121003145819 |dateformat=iso }}, 2011 May 9, Retrieved 2011 May 9</ref>其中至少四人在被关押后死亡。<ref>Staff writer (14 April 2011).  [http://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5gtoQZSUuPajlIrCsMXhxTBeI0Ntg?docId=CNG.02e59dd6cb2c6353408522f79d0dd27f.7f1 "US Concerned by Deaths of Detainees in Bahrain"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5gtoQZSUuPajlIrCsMXhxTBeI0Ntg?docId=CNG.02e59dd6cb2c6353408522f79d0dd27f.7f1 |date=20130623035055 }}.  [[Agence_France-Presse|Agence France-Presse]] (via [[Google_News|Google News]]).  Retrieved 19 April 2011.</ref>

